# ============================================================
# LIFE.TXT  -  one big text file (OBTF): journal, ideas, notes, and todos,
# in one chronological stream. Structure comes from :tags:, not separate files.
#
# Entry format:   YYYY-MM-DD Day | free text here :tag:tag:
# Separator:      a *** line between entries (visual only; agenda ignores it).
#
# Tag style: LIFE.TXT uses :tag: (Org-mode style). calendar.txt uses
# @tag (todo.txt style). The difference is intentional - each file follows
# its own lineage, and here the :tag: colons delimit tags within free-form
# prose, where @ alone could be ambiguous against ordinary words.
#
# How agenda reads this file:
#   open todo      = a line with :todo:    and NOT :done:
#   open waiting   = a line with :waiting: and NOT :done:
#   closed item    = add :done: in place; it then drops out of agenda
#   due follow-up  = add  due:YYYY-MM-DD  to a line; agenda surfaces it LOUD
#                    within its lead window (see: agenda --help)
#
# NOTE: This is a template. Example dates are illustrative - replace with
# your own. Location is adjustable: agenda reads it from $LIFE_DIR
# (default ~/life, so ~/life/LIFE.TXT); set LIFE_DIR to point elsewhere,
# e.g. /mnt/usbflashdrive/life/LIFE.TXT on a machine using a USB drive.
# ============================================================

